1. Microcontroller Arduino Uno for handling input/output and processing authentication logic.
2. Input Modules: 
-  4x4 Matrix Keypad – Used for passcode input.
-  Fingerprint Sensor (R307 or AS608) for biometric authentication.
3. Output & Feedback Modules
-  LCD Display (I2C Module Recommended) – Displays status messages.
-  Buzzer Module – Provides feedback for successful/failed authentication.
-  LED Indicator – red for incorrect attempt, green for success).
4. Lock Mechanism
- Servo Motor: Can be used for prototyping a simple lock mechanism.
5. Power Supply Module
- 5V/12V Power Supply Adapter.

Prototype Wiring Overview
Keypad & Fingerprint Sensor: Arduino Inputs
Servo Motor: Arduino Output.
LCD Display & Buzzer: Feedback System
